---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<section class="intro">
				<p>
					The internet is entering a new phase. AI agents act, negotiate, and
					create value alongside humans. Autonomous workflows replace manual
					coordination. Reputation becomes programmable. Ownership shifts from
					platforms to individuals and their agents.
				</p>
				<p>
					Agentic Web is a field journal that studies these shifts. It
					examines the protocols, systems, and ideas that will shape how
					humans and AI agents build the next internet together.
				</p>
			</section>
			<section class="topics">
				<h2>What we cover</h2>
				<ul>
					<li>
						<strong>Essays</strong> &mdash; Long-form arguments and thesis
						pieces on agent-native economies, coordination systems, and
						internet-native work.
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Notes</strong> &mdash; Short observations, definitions,
						and emerging patterns from the edge of the agentic web.
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Research</strong> &mdash; Breakdowns of tools, protocols,
						papers, frameworks, markets, and infrastructure.
					</li>
				</ul>
			</section>
			<section class="start">
				<h2>Where to start</h2>
				<p>
					Browse the <a href="/archive">archive</a> for all published writing,
					or dive into a category: <a href="/essays">Essays</a>,
					<a href="/notes">Notes</a>, or <a href="/research">Research</a>.
				</p>
			</section>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
<style>
	.intro {
		font-size: 1.1em;
		max-width: 600px;
		margin: 2em auto;
	}
	.topics {
		max-width: 600px;
		margin: 2em auto;
	}
	.topics ul {
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
	}
	.topics li {
		margin-bottom: 1em;
		padding-left: 0;
	}
	.start {
		max-width: 600px;
		margin: 2em auto;
	}
</style>
